url -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh

Start the daemon
#sudo systemctl enable --now tailscaled

Check status:
#sudo systemctl status tailscaled

Connect to your tailnet
#sudo tailscale up

Basic Commands
Check connection status
#tailscale status

Show your Tailscale IP
#tailscale ip

IPv4 only:
#tailscale ip -4

IPv6 only:
tailscale ip -6

View version
#tailscale version

Network diagnostics
#tailscale netcheck

Ping another Tailscale device
#tailscale ping hostname

Example:
tailscale ping server1

List available exit nodes:
#tailscale exit-node list

Get a recommended exit node:
#tailscale exit-node suggest

File Transfer (Taildrop)
Send a file:
#tailscale file cp myfile.txt hostname:

Receive files:
#tailscale file get .
Login / Logout

Logout:
#tailscale logout

Login again:
#tailscale login

Disconnect / Reconnect
Disconnect:
#sudo tailscale down

Reconnect:
#sudo tailscale up

Update Tailscale
#sudo tailscale update

Update without prompts:
#sudo tailscale update --yes

Useful Ubuntu Troubleshooting Commands
Check daemon logs:
#sudo journalctl -u tailscaled -f

Restart Tailscale:
#sudo systemctl restart tailscaled

Verify daemon is running:
#sudo systemctl is-active tailscaled

To see all available commands:
#tailscale --help

or for a specific command:
#tailscale status --help

